THERE, PLEASE OPEN UP!

75
00:06:41,250 --> 00:06:44,625
- Yuto: AXELA ASKED US TO COME
HERE. THIS ISN'T A TRAP.

76
00:06:44,708 --> 00:06:48,125
THERE'S ONLY THE TWO OF US.
COULD YOU PLEASE OPEN THE DOOR?

77
00:06:54,583 --> 00:06:56,750
- Andy: DON'T SHOOT, OKAY?

78
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:58,625
I'M ANDY ANDERSON AND
I'M HELPING THIS GUY

79
00:06:58,708 --> 00:06:59,833
GET YOU BACK SAFELY.

80
00:06:59,916 --> 00:07:02,500
- IT'S ALL RIGHT.
PLEASE. COME WITH US.

81
00:07:07,125 --> 00:07:08,958
WE GOT HER.

82
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:11,250
- INTEGRA!

83
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:15,000
INTEGRA!

84
00:07:15,083 --> 00:07:18,791
- AXELA! I'M GLAD YOU'RE OKAY.
I WAS REALLY WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

85
00:07:18,875 --> 00:07:21,916
- OH, THANK GOD, YOU'RE ALRIGHT!

86
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,250
- WOULD YOU MIND TELLING
ME WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

87
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:28,333
- OH, IT'S JUST, AXELA WAS
NICE ENOUGH TO HELP ME OUT

88
00:07:28,416 --> 00:07:31,041
ONCE WHEN I WAS HAVING
A LITTLE BIT OF TROUBLE.

89
00:07:31,125 --> 00:07:32,375
SO WHEN I FOUND HER,

90
00:07:32,458 --> 00:07:35,041
I THOUGHT IT WAS ONLY
RIGHT TO RETURN THE FAVOR.

91
00:07:35,125 --> 00:07:36,500
- FAIR ENOUGH.

92
00:07:36,583 --> 00:07:39,166
BUT A HUNTER AND A BAND OF
THIEVES WORKING TOGETHER?

93
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:40,666
- I WONDER WHAT THE
INTELLIGENCE COUNCIL

94
00:07:40,750 --> 00:07:42,083
WOULD THINK ABOUT ALL THIS.

95
00:07:42,166 --> 00:07:45,125
- SCREW THEM! WHO CARES
WHAT THE DAMN COUNCIL THINKS.

96
00:07:45,208 --> 00:07:46,708
- I GUESS, YOU'RE RIGHT.

97
00:07:46,791 --> 00:07:49,666
- WE GOT THE BASIC IDEA OF WHAT
HAPPENED FROM YOUR FRIEND HERE.

98
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:54,125
NOW HOW ABOUT YOU START FILLING
US IN ON SOME OF THE DETAILS.

99
00:07:54,208 --> 00:07:59,916
HOW CAN ROSE STILL BE ALIVE?
WHY IS SHE WORKING FOR R.U.C?

100
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:04,458
AND WHO'S THIS GUY?
THIS OPERATIONS DIRECTOR?

101
00:08:04,541 --> 00:08:07,000
WHAT DOES HE HAVE
TO GAIN FROM ALL THIS?

102
00:08:11,333 --> 00:08:12,958
- BY YOUR SILENCE, I TAKE IT,

103
00:08:13,041 --> 00:08:15,750
YOU DON'T KNOW THE ANSWERS
TO ANY OF THESE QUESTIONS.

104
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:17,291
- COME ON! YOU WORKED THERE!

105
00:08:17,375 --> 00:08:20,000
IS THIS THE KIND OF THING THAT
HAPPENS ALL THE TIME? HUH?

106
00:08:20,083 --> 00:08:23,166
DID YOU TALK TO ROSE? I JUST
FIND IT HARD TO BELIEVE THAT YOU

107
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:25,416
COULD BE SO IN THE DARK
ABOUT ALL THIS!

108
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:29,333
- SORRY. I JUST DON'T KNOW.
- THIS IS GETTING US NOWHERE.

109
00:08:29,416 --> 00:08:32,625
- ARE YOU SURE? YOU DON'T KNOW
ANY MORE THAN YOU'VE TOLD US?

110
00:08:32,708 --> 00:08:35,416
- NO. WE'RE TRYING TO FIGURE
THIS OUT, SAME AS YOU.

111
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,416
ALL I KNOW IS THIS,
THE DATA'S BEEN TAMPERED WITH

112
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:40,291
AND OUR ACCESS TO THE HOST
COMPUTER HAS BEEN RESTRICTED.

113
00:08:40,375 --> 00:08:43,166
WE JUST WANT TO CLEAR OUR NAMES
OF THESE FALSE ACCUSATIONS!

114
00:08:43,250 --> 00:08:45,291
- ( scoffs )
FALSE ACCUSATIONS? LOOK AT YOU!

115
00:08:45,375 --> 00:08:46,541
YOU'RE ALL OVER THE NEWS!

116
00:08:46,625 --> 00:08:49,541
FOOTAGE OF YOU KILLING
THAT LADY IN COLD BLOOD!

117
00:08:49,625 --> 00:08:51,958
- IF YOU'RE GOING TO FALL
FOR FALSIFIED DATA LIKE THAT,

118
00:08:52,041 --> 00:08:54,000
I GUESS YOU'RE NOT AS SMART OF
A THIEF AS I THOUGHT YOU WERE.

119
00:08:54,083 --> 00:08:56,250
- WHAT'D YOU SAY?
- STOP IT, ANDY.

120
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:57,625
ROY. BE REALISTIC.

121
00:08:57,708 --> 00:09:00,166
WHY SHOULD THESE GIRLS
WANT TO TELL US ANYTHING?

122
00:09:00,250 --> 00:09:01,708
IF THEY'RE HIDING INFORMATION,

123
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:03,500
THEY'LL SHARE IT
WHEN THEY'RE READY.

124
00:09:03,583 --> 00:09:04,208
- YEAH. YEAH.

125
00:09:04,291 --> 00:09:05,625
- IT'S HORRIBLE.

126
00:09:05,708 --> 00:09:08,208
IF ONLY THERE WAS SOME WAY
TO SPEAK TO ROSE DIRECTLY.

127
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:09,291
- YEAH.

128
00:09:09,375 --> 00:09:11,041
- IT ALL COMES BACK TO ROSE.

129
00:09:11,125 --> 00:09:13,625
SEEMS LIKE THIS WHOLE
SCREWED UP SITUATION

130
00:09:13,708 --> 00:09:16,333
GOT STARTED THE DAY,
SHE SHOWED UP AT R.U.C.

131
00:09:16,416 --> 00:09:18,166
SO IF WE'RE GOING
TO FIGURE THIS OUT,

132
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:20,541
SHE'S OBVIOUSLY THE KEY.

133
00:09:23,041 --> 00:09:24,291
- SOUNDS REASONABLE.

134
00:09:24,375 --> 00:09:27,250
LET'S CONTINUE OUR
INVESTIGATION FROM THAT ANGLE.

135
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,750
- SO WHAT SHOULD WE
DO WITH THESE TWO?

136
00:09:29,833 --> 00:09:33,500
- HEY, ROY? I COULD...
- GO AHEAD IT'S OKAY.

137
00:09:34,875 --> 00:09:36,250
I'LL LEAVE THEM TO YOU, SOLTY.

138
00:09:36,333 --> 00:09:38,500
- ( exclaims ) MIRANDA?

139
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,333
- FINE. WHY DON'T YOU SHOW THEM
TO THE EMPTY UNIT DOWNSTAIRS?

140
00:09:42,416 --> 00:09:43,541
- LOOK THAT'S REALLY
NOT NECESSARY.

141
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:44,750
- WAIT A MINUTE!

142
00:09:44,833 --> 00:09:46,666
DON'T YOU REALIZE YOU'RE
HARBORING CRIMINALS?

143
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,875
- OH, YEAH. I GUESS IT'LL BE
JUST LIKE HARBORING YOU.

144
00:09:48,958 --> 00:09:52,000
- WHAT? HEY! DON'T PUT ME
IN THE SAME CATEGORY AS...

145
00:09:52,083 --> 00:09:54,875
- I'M HUNGRY! WHAT ARE WE GOING
TO DO ABOUT DINNER, SOLTY?

146
00:09:54,958 --> 00:09:57,958
- OH, THAT'S RIGHT!
SORRY ABOUT THAT.

147
00:09:58,041 --> 00:10:00,958
I'D FORGOTTEN ALL ABOUT DINNER.
I'LL GO GET IT STARTED.

148
00:10:01,041 --> 00:10:03,291
- WELL, HURRY IT UP!
- Miranda: KASHA!

149
00:10:03,375 --> 00:10:05,500
- SOLTY? WOULD YOU MIND
IF I GIVE YOU A HAND?

150
00:10:05,583 --> 00:10:10,333
- AXELA! WHAT ARE YOU DOING!
- SURE! THAT'D BE GREAT!

151
00:10:10,416 --> 00:10:12,500
- THANKS YOU WOULDN'T BY
CHANCE HAPPEN TO HAVE

152
00:10:12,583 --> 00:10:14,750
-WAIT.
-THOSE LAUREL LEAVES.

153
00:10:23,291 --> 00:10:26,250
- ISN'T THIS NICE?
US, COOKING TOGETHER?

154
00:10:26,333 --> 00:10:29,208
- YES, IT IS! THANK YOU, SOLTY.

155
00:10:29,875 --> 00:10:32,625
- DON'T MENTION IT.

156
00:10:32,708 --> 00:10:36,208
- OH, WAIT A MINUTE. YOU NEED
TO CUT THEM INTO SMALLER PIECES.

157
00:10:36,291 --> 00:10:37,333
- I DO?

158
00:10:37,416 --> 00:10:38,750
- OH YEAH. IF THE
PIECES ARE TOO BIG,

159
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:40,125
THEN THEY WON'T COOK EVENLY.

160
00:10:40,208 --> 00:10:42,125
- OH, I GUESS I
DIDN'T KNOW THAT.

161
00:10:42,208 --> 00:10:44,416
- ( chuckles ) IT'S A
COMMON MISTAKE ACTUALLY.

162
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:45,541
- HEY.

163
00:10:46,833 --> 00:10:50,083
I WAS, I WAS WONDERING
IF I COULD TALK TO YOU?

164
00:10:51,416 --> 00:10:54,333
- I SEE.
SO THIS IS ABOUT SILVIA?

165
00:10:54,416 --> 00:10:57,125
- SHE WAS, I MEAN WE...

166
00:10:57,208 --> 00:11:00,125
- THE TWO OF YOU WERE FRIENDS,
WEREN'T YOU?

167
00:11:00,208 --> 00:11:03,333
- YES. EVER SINCE
THAT ONE DAY, I GUESS.

168
00:11:03,416 --> 00:11:06,375
WE TRIED TO KEEP IN TOUCH.
SHE WAS A GROWN-UP,

169
00:11:06,458 --> 00:11:09,625
BUT SHE STILL ACTED LIKE
A LITTLE KID SOMETIMES.

170
00:11:09,708 --> 00:11:12,166
SOMETIMES SHE'D TAKE ME
OUT FOR SOME ICE CREAM.

171
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:14,000
SHE WAS SO NICE TO ME.

172
00:11:14,083 --> 00:11:15,458
( crying )

173
00:11:15,541 --> 00:11:17,708
- IT'S OKAY.
- WHY'D SHE HAVE TO DIE?

174
00:11:19,416 --> 00:11:22,666
- DON'T WORRY KASHA.
WE ARE GOING TO GET THIS MAN.

175
