WOULD YOU MIND GOING
BY MY SISTER'S GRAVE

219
00:13:45,166 --> 00:13:46,666
AND TIDYING THINGS UP A BIT?

220
00:13:46,750 --> 00:13:50,250
JUST ONCE A YEAR WOULD BE FINE.
JUST TRY TO KEEP THE WEEDS AWAY,

221
00:13:50,333 --> 00:13:53,041
AND MAKE SURE, YOU CAN
STILL SEE HER NAME AND ALL THAT.

222
00:13:53,125 --> 00:13:58,041
OKAY? I APPRECIATE IT.
OH, AND ONE MORE THING.

223
00:13:58,125 --> 00:14:00,041
OH, DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT!

224
00:14:00,125 --> 00:14:03,666
THAT WAS ALL I
REALLY WANTED TO SAY.

225
00:14:03,750 --> 00:14:06,541
THAT'S IT THEN. GOODBYE.

226
00:14:09,250 --> 00:14:11,333
- ( crying )

227
00:14:16,541 --> 00:14:17,541
CELICA...

228
00:14:26,041 --> 00:14:27,500
- ( sighs )

229
00:15:03,625 --> 00:15:04,666
- ROSE!

230
00:15:11,041 --> 00:15:13,625
- TELL ME WHAT DO
YOU WANT TO DO?

231
00:15:14,625 --> 00:15:17,000
- WHAT WOULD YOU
LIKE FOR ME TO DO?

232
00:15:17,083 --> 00:15:20,166
- IT'S NOT FAIR TO ANSWER
A QUESTION WITH A QUESTION.

233
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:24,291
DO YOU HAVE SOMETHING IN MIND?

234
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,041
- YES.

235
00:15:26,125 --> 00:15:28,541
- YOU BELIEVE IN YOURSELF,
DON'T YOU?

236
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:31,666
- YES.
- THEN WHY?

237
00:15:31,750 --> 00:15:36,000
WHY DO YOU LOOK SO UNCERTAIN?
EVERYONE MAKES MISTAKES.

238
00:15:36,083 --> 00:15:38,250
PEOPLE DO, MACHINES DO.

239
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:41,666
WHAT'S IMPORTANT IS,
TO NOT REPEAT THOSE MISTAKES.

240
00:15:41,750 --> 00:15:44,375
TO BE ABLE TO LEARN
FROM THOSE PAST EXPERIENCES

241
00:15:44,458 --> 00:15:47,041
AND ALLOW THEIR OUTCOME
TO GUIDE YOU.

242
00:15:47,125 --> 00:15:49,333
YOU HAVE TO USE YOUR
ABILITIES TO THE FULLEST,

243
00:15:49,416 --> 00:15:50,791
AND DO YOUR BEST.

244
00:15:50,875 --> 00:15:52,958
THAT WAY, YOU WILL
HAVE NO REGRETS.

245
00:15:53,041 --> 00:15:56,541
IF YOU CAN DO THAT, THEN
YOU CAN START YOUR FUTURE.

246
00:15:58,375 --> 00:16:01,041
- THEN COME WITH ME.
- YES.

247
00:16:01,125 --> 00:16:03,416
- TO THE FUTURE.
- YES.

248
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:04,541
- TOGETHER.

249
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:22,125
- ( phone ringing )

250
00:16:23,041 --> 00:16:24,041
- YES?

251
00:16:24,708 --> 00:16:25,958
WHAT IS IT?

252
00:16:26,041 --> 00:16:27,583
- Woman: I'M SORRY
TO DISTURB YOU SIR,

253
00:16:27,666 --> 00:16:30,291
BUT WE SEEM TO HAVE
A SITUATION IN THE LOBBY.

254
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:33,500
- I SAID LET GO OF ME!

255
00:16:33,583 --> 00:16:35,583
WHERE THE HECK
DO YOU THINK YOU ARE, OLD MAN?

256
00:16:35,666 --> 00:16:37,375
- ROSE, JUST LISTEN TO ME!

257
00:16:37,458 --> 00:16:39,666
- STOP IT!
YOU'RE MAKING A SCENE!

258
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:40,833
- ROSE...

259
00:16:40,916 --> 00:16:42,833
- HAVE YOU FORGOTTEN
WHAT YOU SAID TO ME?

260
00:16:42,916 --> 00:16:44,041
YOU SAID AS LONG
AS I WAS ALIVE,

261
00:16:44,125 --> 00:16:46,375
YOU WOULDN'T CARE
ABOUT WHAT I DID.

262
00:16:46,458 --> 00:16:48,583
WELL I'M ALIVE,
SO WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

263
00:16:48,666 --> 00:16:51,166
ARE WE DONE HERE?
GOOD. GLAD WE HAD THIS TALK.

264
00:16:51,250 --> 00:16:54,125
- NO! WE'RE NOT DONE!
TURN AROUND AND TALK TO ME!

265
00:16:55,291 --> 00:16:57,541
- SORRY, BUT I'VE GOT
A LOT OF WORK TO DO.

266
00:16:57,625 --> 00:16:59,333
- WAIT!

267
00:16:59,416 --> 00:17:02,833
- EXCUSE ME SIR,
BUT THIS IS A PLACE OF BUSINESS.

268
00:17:02,916 --> 00:17:06,708
I'M GOING TO HAVE TO ASK YOU
TO REFRAIN FROM SUCH BEHAVIOR.

269
00:17:07,791 --> 00:17:10,000
- AND WHO IN THE HELL,
MIGHT YOU BE?

270
00:17:10,083 --> 00:17:12,750
- FIRST, MIGHT I ASK YOUR
RELATIONSHIP TO MS. ANDERSON?

271
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:14,291
- NO, FIRST YOU ANSWER ME!

272
00:17:14,375 --> 00:17:15,958
- VERY WELL. IF YOU INSIST.

273
00:17:16,041 --> 00:17:19,291
I'M THE DIRECTOR OF OPERATIONS
FOR THE SECURITY DIVISION.

274
00:17:19,375 --> 00:17:22,000
HER DIRECT SUPERVISOR HERE,
IN OTHER WORDS.

275
00:17:22,083 --> 00:17:24,000
ASHLEY LYNX.
I'M PLEASED TO MEET YOU.

276
00:17:24,083 --> 00:17:27,833
- ( gasps ) SO YOU'RE THE ONE!

277
00:17:27,916 --> 00:17:29,708
- WE SHOULD TALK.

278
00:17:29,791 --> 00:17:32,750
NOW, WHY DON'T YOU TELL
ME WHAT YOU MEANT BY THAT?

279
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:33,875
- HERE YOU GO, SIR.

280
00:17:35,125 --> 00:17:36,541
- THE TEA LEAVES ARE
GROWN BY OUR COMPANY.

281
00:17:36,625 --> 00:17:38,083
THE TASTE IS RATHER UNIQUE,

282
00:17:38,166 --> 00:17:40,416
AND THE FRAGRANCE
IS QUITE SOOTHING.

283
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:43,000
IT'S ONE OF MY FAVORITE BLENDS.

284
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:47,458
- I'M TAKING ROSE HOME.
- SORRY?

285
00:17:47,541 --> 00:17:49,541
- YOU HEARD ME.
SHE'S MY DAUGHTER.

286
00:17:49,625 --> 00:17:52,458
NOW CALL HER DOWN HERE,
SO WE CAN GO.

287
00:17:52,541 --> 00:17:54,958
- AH! SO THE TEA IS NOT
TO YOUR LIKING, I TAKE IT?

288
00:17:56,125 --> 00:17:58,291
PERHAPS YOU'D LIKE TO
TRY SOMETHING DIFFERENT?

289
00:17:58,375 --> 00:18:00,166
- YOU GET HER IN HERE!
RIGHT NOW!

290
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:02,208
- IT'S NOT NECESSARY
TO RAISE YOUR VOICE.

291
00:18:02,291 --> 00:18:03,625
I'M NOT DEAF, YOU KNOW.

292
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:04,791
- FINE. SO GET HER ALREADY.

293
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:06,541
- I'M AFRAID THAT'S
NOT POSSIBLE.

294
00:18:06,625 --> 00:18:08,791
ROSE IS ACTUALLY BUSY
WORKING AT THE MOMENT.

295
00:18:08,875 --> 00:18:10,416
BUT I WOULD BE MORE
THAN HAPPY TO ADDRESS

296
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:12,333
ANY CONCERNS YOU MIGHT HAVE.

297
00:18:16,083 --> 00:18:17,208
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

298
00:18:17,291 --> 00:18:18,666
- IF YOU WON'T CALL
HER DOWN HERE,

299
00:18:18,750 --> 00:18:21,000
THEN I'LL FIND HERMYSELF.
-OUTSIDERS AREN'T

300
00:18:21,083 --> 00:18:23,583
ALLOWED TO ROAM AROUND
THE BUILDING UNATTENDED.

301
00:18:23,666 --> 00:18:25,541
- I AM NOT GOING TO
LET ROSE STAY HERE

302
00:18:25,625 --> 00:18:26,916
AND WORK WITH SOMEONE LIKE YOU.

303
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,958
- SOMEONE LIKE ME?
APPARENTLY YOU'VE

304
00:18:29,041 --> 00:18:31,416
DEVELOPED A SOMEWHAT
OF A DEEP LOATHING FOR ME.

305
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:34,375
- DEVELOPED, HUH?
IT'S PRETTY EASY TO LOATHE

306
00:18:34,458 --> 00:18:36,250
SOMEONE WHO KILLS
HIS EMPLOYEES.

307
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,791
- I'M SURE I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU MEAN.

308
00:18:38,875 --> 00:18:41,125
BUT I'M CURIOUS YOU
WOULDN'T HAPPEN TO KNOW

309
00:18:41,208 --> 00:18:42,583
ANYTHING CONCERNING
THE WHEREABOUTS OF

310
00:18:42,666 --> 00:18:45,208
MY FORMER SUBORDINATES?

311
00:18:45,291 --> 00:18:46,833
I'D BE GRATEFUL FOR
ANY INFORMATION

312
00:18:46,916 --> 00:18:48,333
YOU HAVE ABOUT THEM.

313
00:18:48,416 --> 00:18:50,250
IT'S A CITIZEN'S
DUTY TO COOPERATE

314
00:18:50,333 --> 00:18:52,125
WITH A POLICE INVESTIGATION.

315
00:18:52,208 --> 00:18:54,916
- I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.
- OH, IS THAT SO?

316
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,208
- AND EVEN IF I DID,
I WOULDN'T TELL YOU.

317
00:18:57,291 --> 00:18:59,041
- AND WHY WOULD THAT BE?

318
00:19:02,166 --> 00:19:05,333
- LIKE I SAID,
'CAUSE I DON'T LIKE YOU.

319
00:19:05,416 --> 00:19:07,500
- AND I FIND YOU UNPLEASANT,
AS WELL.

320
00:19:10,458 --> 00:19:13,125
LISTEN CAREFULLY MR. REVANT.

321
00:19:13,208 --> 00:19:15,791
I WOULD REMIND YOU THAT R.U.C
CONTROLS THE GOVERNMENT

322
00:19:15,875 --> 00:19:17,375
AND THE ECONOMY OF THIS CITY.

323
00:19:18,166 --> 00:19:19,791
- SO? WHAT DO I CARE?

324
00:19:19,875 --> 00:19:22,500
- IT WOULD BE BEST FOR YOU
TO MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS.

325
00:19:22,583 --> 00:19:25,708
- OTHERWISE, YOU AND THOSE
AROUND YOU MIGHT GET HURT.

326
00:19:25,791 --> 00:19:26,916
- WHAT WAS THAT?

327
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:30,958
- STAY OUT OF IT.
DO I MAKE MYSELF CLEAR?

328
00:19:31,041 --> 00:19:32,833
- IS THAT SOME KIND OF THREAT?

329
00:19:32,916 --> 00:19:36,000
- THAT ALL DEPENDS ON
WHAT YOU DO, MR. REVANT.

330
00:19:36,083 --> 00:19:37,583
LEAVE THROUGH THE BACK EXIT.

331
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:40,875
WOULD YOU LIKE
SOMEONE TO ESCORT YOU?

332
00:19:46,208 --> 00:19:47,750
( laughing )

333
00:20:19,583 --> 00:20:21,666
- ( phone ringing )

334
00:20:25,541 --> 00:20:28,291
- Automated voice: NO ONE IS
AVAILABLE TO TAKE YOUR CALL.

335
00:20:28,375 --> 00:20:30,333
PLEASE LEAVE A MESSAGE
AFTER THE TONE.

336
00:20:30,416 --> 00:20:32,041
- ( beeps )

337
00:20:32,125 --> 00:20:35,125
- ROY REVANT. THIS IS JOSEPH.

338
00:20:35,208 --> 00:20:38,958
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND THAT
I TRACKED DOWN YOUR NUMBER.

339
00:20:39,041 --> 00:20:41,291
SOME PEOPLE PAID
A VISIT TO MY HOME RECENTLY.

340
00:20:41,375 --> 00:20:43,791
- THAT VOICE.
WHERE HAVE I HEARD IT BEFORE...

341
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:45,625
- IT SEEMS ASHLEY IS TAKING
NO CHANCES THIS TIME.

342
00:20:45,708 --> 00:20:47,208
- ( gasps )

343
00:20:47,291 --> 00:20:49,833
- Man 1: GREAT. ANOTHER FAILURE.
- Man 2: I'VE TRIED EVERYTHING!

344
00:20:49,916 --> 00:20:51,583
- Man 3: YOU HAVE GOT
TO LOWER THE FATALITY RATE!

345
00:20:51,666 --> 00:20:53,625
- Man 4: AFTER ALL OUR EFFORTS,
WE'VE STILL HAD NO SUCCESS.

346
00:20:53,708 --> 00:20:55,083
- I SINCERELY BELIEVE
THAT THIS METHOD

347
00:20:55,166 --> 00:20:57,833
OF AUGMENTING THE
GENES IS ENTIRELY WRONG.

348
00:20:57,916 --> 00:21:01,208
ASHLEY, ARE YOU
EVEN LISTENING TO ME?

349
00:21:01,291 --> 00:21:04,708
- IT WAS HIM! THE OPERATIONS
DIRECTOR WAS THERE!

350
00:21:04,791 --> 00:21:06,208
- I'VE SHIPPED A PACKAGE TO YOU.

351
00:21:06,291 --> 00:21:08,333
I THINK YOU WILL FIND
IT'S CONTENTS USEFUL.

352
00:21:08,416 --> 00:21:11,666
GOOD LUCK. GIVE MY BEST
REGARDS TO THAT GIRL.

353
00:21:12,375 --> 00:21:14,416
- HELLO? HELLO?

354
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:15,458
- ( dial tone )

355
00:21:20,166 --> 00:21:23,333
- HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON?

356
00:21:23,416 --> 00:21:24,916
- SOLTY! I NEED TO ASK YOU

357
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,208
- SOMETHING!
- WHAT IS IT?

358
00:21:26,291 --> 00:21:28,291
- DO YOU KNOW
A MAN NAMED JOSEPH?

359
00:21:28,375 --> 00:21:31,125
- YES. BUT WHY?
DID SOMETHING HAPPEN TO HIM?

360
00:21:31,208 --> 00:21:33,875
- YOU HAVE TO TELL
ME WHERE HE IS! PLEASE!

361
00:21:39,541 --> 00:21:42,250
- TWELVE LONG YEARS HAVE
PASSED, MY DEAREST ONE.

362
00:21:43,458 --> 00:21:47,791
BUT THIS TIME, I WILL COME
FOR YOU WITHOUT FAIL.

363
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:50,291
ILLUMINA.

364
00:22:00,416 --> 00:22:03,166
- ( theme song playing )

365
00:22:08,958 --> 00:22:10,708
- ( singing in Japanese )

366
00:23:33,041 --> 00:23:34,333
- ( music playing )

367
00:23:34,416 --> 00:23:36,666
- Solty: WHAT IS GOING
ON WITH YOU, ROSE?

368
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:38,333
- Rose: THAT'S NONE
OF YOUR BUSINESS.

369
00:23:38,416 --> 00:23:41,500
- Solty: NEXT EPISODE,
"CATASTROPHE CALLS."

370
00:23:41,583 --> 00:23:44,083
YOU WILL COME BACK, WON'T YOU?

